  "body_text": null,
  "page": null,
  "source": "[\\set.theoretic.pair:of{a}:and{b}]\nDefines: P is \\set\nwhen: a, b is \\set\nexpresses:\n. forAll: x is \\set\n  then:\n  . have:\n    . anyOf:\n      . x = a\n      . x = b\n    iff: x \"in\" P\nDocumented:\n. called: \"pair of $a?$ and $b?$\"\n. written: \"\\{a?, b?\\}\"\n. description: \"The set $\\{a, b\\}$ containing precisely $a$ and $b$, guaranteed by the axiom of pairing: if $a$ and $b$ are sets, then there exists a set containing precisely $a$ and $b$.\"\nId: \"9f79d83e-8423-4343-b547-e391b3305994\"",
